    <item>
      <title>Open Settings</title>
      <link>/docs/configuration/open-settings/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/docs/configuration/open-settings/</guid>
      <description>&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Open Settings from menu bar.&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;      &lt;img&#xA;        src=&#34;/docs/configuration/open-settings/images/menu-icon@2x.png&#34;&#xA;        alt=&#34;menu-icon@2x.png&#34;&#xA;        style=&#34;width: 268px&#34;&#xA;      /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-primary&#34; role=&#34;alert&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 class=&#34;alert-heading&#34;&gt;Note&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;p&gt;If you&amp;rsquo;ve hidden the menu bar icon, open ShowyEdge again from Apps while ShowyEdge is already running to open Settings window.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;  &lt;img&#xA;    src=&#34;/docs/configuration/open-settings/images/apps@2x.png&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;apps@2x.png&#34;&#xA;    style=&#34;width: 400px&#34;&#xA;  /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Input source color configuration</title>
      <link>/docs/configuration/color-configuration/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/docs/configuration/color-configuration/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;You can change indicator colors of input sources.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;../open-settings/&#34;&gt;Open Settings&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Press &lt;code&gt;Set the color for ...&lt;/code&gt; button on Settings.&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;      &lt;img&#xA;        src=&#34;/docs/configuration/color-configuration/images/add-color@2x.png&#34;&#xA;        alt=&#34;add-color@2x.png&#34;&#xA;        style=&#34;width: 600px&#34;&#xA;      /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Change colors.&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;      &lt;img&#xA;        src=&#34;/docs/configuration/color-configuration/images/change-color@2x.png&#34;&#xA;        alt=&#34;change-color@2x.png&#34;&#xA;        style=&#34;width: 600px&#34;&#xA;      /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Indicator size configuration</title>
      <link>/docs/configuration/indicator-size-configuration/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/docs/configuration/indicator-size-configuration/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;basic&#34;&gt;Basic&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You can change the indicator height.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;../open-settings/&#34;&gt;Open Settings&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Choose &lt;code&gt;Indicator&lt;/code&gt; from the sidebar.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Adjust height.&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;      &lt;img&#xA;        src=&#34;/docs/configuration/indicator-size-configuration/images/indicator-height@2x.png&#34;&#xA;        alt=&#34;indicator-height@2x.png&#34;&#xA;        style=&#34;width: 600px&#34;&#xA;      /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;advanced&#34;&gt;Advanced&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You can put the indicator by custom size and origin.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;../open-settings/&#34;&gt;Open Settings&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Choose &lt;code&gt;Custom Frame&lt;/code&gt; from the sidebar.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Enable &lt;code&gt;Use custom frame&lt;/code&gt;, and then adjust the indicator size and origin.&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;      &lt;img&#xA;        src=&#34;/docs/configuration/indicator-size-configuration/images/indicator-size@2x.png&#34;&#xA;        alt=&#34;indicator-size@2x.png&#34;&#xA;        style=&#34;width: 600px&#34;&#xA;      /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;tips&#34;&gt;Tips&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;You can specify size by pixel or percentage of screen.&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;(e.g., width = 100%, height = 20pt)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Choose &lt;code&gt;Lower-Left&lt;/code&gt; from origin options if you want to put indicator to the bottom of screen.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Indicator options</title>
      <link>/docs/configuration/indicator-options/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/docs/configuration/indicator-options/</guid>
      <description>&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Hide indicator when the menu bar is hidden.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Show indicator behind app windows.&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;This option is useful with &lt;a href=&#34;/docs/configuration/indicator-size-configuration/#advanced&#34;&gt;the custom frame&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;&#xA;You can use the Desktop background as an indicator.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;  &lt;img&#xA;    src=&#34;/docs/configuration/indicator-options/images/indicator-options@2x.png&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;indicator-options@2x.png&#34;&#xA;    style=&#34;width: 600px&#34;&#xA;  /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;follow-active-window-position&#34;&gt;Follow active window position&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This option allows the indicator to track the title bar of the currently active window.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;  &lt;img&#xA;    src=&#34;/docs/configuration/indicator-options/images/follow-settings@2x.png&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;follow-settings@2x.png&#34;&#xA;    style=&#34;width: 600px&#34;&#xA;  /&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;As shown in the screenshot below, the indicator will appear on the title bar.&#xA;Settings for the indicator height and custom frame will also be applied as usual.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Open at login</title>
      <link>/docs/configuration/open-at-login/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/docs/configuration/open-at-login/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;You can configure whether ShowyEdge launches at login in Settings.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;../open-settings/&#34;&gt;Open Settings&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Enable &lt;code&gt;Open at login&lt;/code&gt;.&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;      &lt;img&#xA;        src=&#34;/docs/configuration/open-at-login/images/open-at-login@2x.png&#34;&#xA;        alt=&#34;open-at-login@2x.png&#34;&#xA;        style=&#34;width: 600px&#34;&#xA;      /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Hide the icon in menu bar</title>
      <link>/docs/configuration/hide-menu-bar-icon/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/docs/configuration/hide-menu-bar-icon/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This setting allows you to toggle whether or not to display the menu bar icon.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;../open-settings/&#34;&gt;Open Settings&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Turn off &lt;code&gt;Show icon in menu bar&lt;/code&gt;.&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;      &lt;img&#xA;        src=&#34;/docs/configuration/hide-menu-bar-icon/images/hide-menu-bar-icon@2x.png&#34;&#xA;        alt=&#34;hide-menu-bar-icon@2x.png&#34;&#xA;        style=&#34;width: 600px&#34;&#xA;      /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;</description>
    </item>
